I passed by a painting in an older home here in Columbus, GA with a painting probably done in the 70’s of some potted plants.  It was painted by a local artist (who is no longer with us), Mary Passailaigue and I was just TAKEN with it!  Although she passed away around 30 years ago, her granddaughter now owns an local art gallery @highlandgalerie  in Columbus.  It was so fun to try my own take on potted plants grouped together and here is one from the series!  Feel free to click on the link in our profile to get a catalogue of available work from this series with sizes, prices and purchasing info!

Our *New* print “Virginia” is in two different color ways || We moved houses back in November and renovated a 1970’s ranch.  Our house only had one owner before us, and her name was “Virginia”.
